MORRIS & CUMINGS DREDGING COMPANY, Libelant-Appellee, v. SAMUEL ROSOFF CO., Inc., Respondent-Appellee, and Tuarr Contracting Company, Inc., Respondent-Impleaded-Appellant. No. 92. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Dec. 7, 1931. Single & Hill, of New York City (Forrest E. Single, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. James D. Carpenter, Jr., of Jersey City, N. J. (Charles W. Hagen, of New York City, of counsel), for libelant-appellee.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and SWAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Deeree affirmed.
